= Boot Process for BIOS

:toc: left
:icons: font
:sectlinks:

See also: link:index.html[Main Boot Page], link:efi-boot.html[EFI Boot Process], link:../roadmap.html[Roadmap]

[cols=",,,",]
|===
|[.s1]#*Phase*# |[.s1]#*Component*# |[.s1]#*Brief Description*#
|[.s1]#*Hardware/Software Mechanism*#

|[.s1]#*Stage 1*# |[.s1]#*MBR / Boot Sector*# |[.s1]#The first 512 bytes
on disk. Loads the stage2 bootloader in the reserved space of the MBR to
RAM.# |[.s1]#BIOS INT 0x13h (LBA); Signature 0xAA55 at byte 510.#

|[.s1]#*Stage 2*# |[.s1]#*Memory Detection*# |[.s1]#Queries the BIOS for
a list of all usable RAM regions. This is the source for your
memMapAddr.# |[.s1]#BIOS INT 0x15, EAX=0xE820.#

|[.s1]#*Stage 2*# |[.s1]#*A20 Gate*# |[.s1]#Disables the "wraparound" at
1MB to allow access to higher memory which is where the kernel will load
normally.# |[.s1]#"Fast A20" via I/O Port 0x92 or BIOS INT 0x15,
AX=0x2401.#

|[.s1]#*Stage 2*# |[.s1]#*Video Setup*# |[.s1]#(Optional) Sets a
graphical mode (e.g., 1024x768) before BIOS interrupts become
unavailable (reserved for future).# |[.s1]#VESA BIOS Extensions (VBE).#

|[.s1]#*Transition*# |[.s1]#*GDT Setup*# |[.s1]#Defines Global
Descriptor Table with Flat 4GB segments for Code and Data.# |[.s1]#LGDT
instruction; Segment limit 0xFFFFFFFF.#

|[.s1]#*Transition*# |[.s1]#*Protected Mode Switch*# |[.s1]#Flips the
CPU from 16-bit Real Mode to 32-bit Protected Mode.# |[.s1]#Set Bit 0 in
CR0 register; Far JMP to flush pipeline.#

|[.s1]#*Stage 3*# |[.s1]#*Filesystem Parser*# |[.s1]#Navigates the
storage (e.g., FAT32) to find the kernel file under `/boot`
of the host filesystem.# |[.s1]#Custom code to read Root Directory and
Clusters/Extents.#

|[.s1]#*Stage 3*# |[.s1]#*Executable Loader*# |[.s1]#Copies the kernel
binary to its linked destination at 0xa00000.#
|[.s1]#Memory copy; ELF Program Header parsing if using ELF.#

|[.s1]#*Handoff*# |[.s1]#*Info Structure*# |[.s1]#Packs the memory map
and boot parameters into a struct for the C parser.# |[.s1]#Populating a
memory region (e.g., 0x7000) with packed data.#

|[.s1]#*Handoff*# |[.s1]#*Final Jump*# |[.s1]#Sets EAX to your magic
value, EBX to the info pointer, and jumps to the kernel.# |[.s1]#mov
eax, MAGIC; mov ebx, INFO_PTR; jmp KERNEL_ENTRY.#
|===

== Current Implementation Status

* Stage 1: Full MBR bootsector with LBA INT 13h support, metadata patching via "VLSP" signature
* Stage 2: A20 gate enable, GDT setup, protected mode switch, VGA text output — implemented but stops before filesystem parsing
* Stage 3 (Filesystem Parser, Executable Loader, Handoff): Not yet implemented

